The '''Justice Action Network''', also known as '''Justice Action League''' or simply as '''JAN''', was an [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaanian]] [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] organization founded after the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] by [[Earnst Kamiel]] and the parents of [[Jan Ors]] (who chose the organization's name as an homage to their daughter).

==History==
[[File:JAN_Terrorist.jpg|thumb|left|100px|JAN agent operating in the [[Tapani sector/Legends|Tapani sector]].]]
Opposed to the official policy of pacifism and appeasement chosen for Alderaan by the planetary leader, [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Prestor Organa]], JAN used criminal activities to resist the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Many of its surviving members later joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].

The [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] JAN leader [[Kelsek]] used a [[JAN Camp|camp]] located on [[Mrlsst/Legends|Mrlsst]] in the [[Tapani sector/Legends|Tapani sector]] to train a new strike team before an assault on an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Unidentified Torpedo Sphere (Tallaan)|Torpedo Sphere]] that was docked at [[Tallaan]].

To spread their ideas about a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxywide]] armed revolution against the Empire, JAN made use of [[virastack]] newsfiles, which were notorious for appearing in the middle of military training tapes, holoshows and [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]] racing digests, among other types of holo-broadcasts.

In [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], the group sabotaged and destroyed a luxury starliner that was approaching [[Cadomai Prime/Legends|Cadomai]].<ref name="AJ11">{{JournalCite|11|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>

